09:03.250 --> 09:06.708
- A skunk? Is that venomous?
- No, Just malodorous.

09:06.790 --> 09:09.839
As luck would have it,
my friend John Quincy Myers is visiting.

09:09.920 --> 09:12.002
He's a man of the wild
who can rid your mongrel of the stench.

09:13.340 --> 09:14.420
Thank you, Great-Aunt.

09:15.090 --> 09:17.502
Ulysses, will you ask Myers to meet Ian

09:17.600 --> 09:18.885
at the front of the house,
near the jetty?

09:18.970 --> 09:20.050
Yes, mistress.

09:20.140 --> 09:22.472
But first, Ulysses,
show my nephew and his bride

09:22.560 --> 09:24.972
to their bedchamber,
where the air will be fresh.

09:25.060 --> 09:26.186
As you wish, mistress.

09:26.270 --> 09:28.647
After your travels, you'll desire
a bit of rest, will ye not?

09:29.480 --> 09:31.971
Aye. Thank ye, Auntie.

09:41.740 --> 09:43.196
It's remarkable, Sassenach.

09:44.330 --> 09:45.319
What is?

09:45.410 --> 09:47.662
The similarities
between Aunt Jocasta and my mother.

09:50.540 --> 09:53.998
Same smile, same manner, their voices.

09:54.420 --> 09:58.459
Always wished ye'd kent my mother,
but having ye meet my aunt is just fine.

10:06.980 --> 10:09.221
This will be your chamber, sir.

10:10.060 --> 10:11.140
Mistress.

10:14.530 --> 10:16.350
I trust all is well?

10:17.780 --> 10:21.238
If a need arises, you may call upon me.

10:24.200 --> 10:25.576
Thank you, Ulysses.

10:27.500 --> 10:28.865
Sir. Mistress.

10:29.540 --> 10:31.838
Please, call me Claire.

10:36.420 --> 10:37.751
Mistress Claire.

10:38.760 --> 10:40.079
What are your names?

10:41.390 --> 10:43.756
I'm Phaedre. That's Mary.

10:44.470 --> 10:46.017
Mistress Claire.

10:47.690 --> 10:49.055
Is there anything else
you'll be needing?

10:49.230 --> 10:51.107
No, thank you.

11:06.120 --> 11:10.659
Sassenach, you haven't had
much to say since our arrival.

11:13.630 --> 11:14.870
Claire...

11:18.090 --> 11:19.216
As ye say,

11:20.800 --> 11:22.791
